@slashfi CEO Victor Cardenas Codriansky is a Venezuelan entrepreneur and fintech founder best known as the co-founder of Slash, a venture-backed financial platform designed for modern startups and online companies. He is also a recipient of the Thiel Fellowship, a prestigious program that supports young founders building ambitious companies. Cardenas was born and raised in Caracas, Venezuela, a country that has faced major economic instability and hyperinflation over the past two decades. Growing up in such an environment shaped his interest in financial systems and the importance of reliable banking infrastructure. Experiencing how unstable currency and financial systems affect everyday life motivated him to explore how technology could improve global financial services. He later moved to the United States to study computer science at Stanford University. While studying there, he became deeply involved in the Silicon Valley startup ecosystem and began building technology products focused on financial services. One of his early projects was a fintech tool designed to help people manage and split shared expenses digitally. Cardenas eventually left Stanford after being selected as a Thiel Fellow, choosing to focus entirely on entrepreneurship. He later co-founded Slash, which aims to provide modern financial infrastructure for startups, online businesses, and creators. The platform offers services such as business banking tools, payment systems, and financial management features tailored to companies operating in the digital economy. Beyond building fintech products, Cardenas is also known for sharing insights about startup culture, productivity, and leadership. He often emphasizes that founders should prioritize mental clarity, good health, and sufficient sleep in order to make better decisions when building companies. His perspective challenges the traditional "hustle culture" narrative and instead focuses on long-term performance and sustainable productivity.
